      <div xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719">
        <head xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Hd1e99" type="question-title">De voluptate</head>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e102">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e112" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e104">Gregorius, <title>in Moralibus</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e112">Qui nunc male se voluptatibus dilatat, eum post
              in suppliciis poena coangustat.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e117">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e127" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e119">Gregorius, in <title>Registro</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e127">Si pro luxu animi, atque voluptate carnis,
              dominico die quis lavari appetit, hoc fieri nec reliquo quolibet die concedimus. Si
              autem pro necessitate corporis, hoc nec dominico die prohibemus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e132">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e142" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e134">Hieronymus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e142">Miseriae deliciis, et deliciae miseriis
              commutantur. In nostro arbitrio est, vel divitem sequi, vel Lazarum.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e147">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e157" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e149">Hieronymus, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e157">Difficile, imo impossibile est, ut praesentibus
              quis, et futuris fruatur bonis: ut hic ventrem, ibi mentem impleat: ut de deliciis
              transeat ad delicias: ut in utroque saeculo primus sit: ut in coelo et in terra
              appareat gloriosus.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e163">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e173" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e165">Bernardus, <title>de Contemptu</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e173">Nunc et trahit sua quemque voluptas, et odorem
              turpis lucri sectantes, <!--<i>-->quaestum aestimant pietatem<!--</i>-->: quorum
              damnatio certa est.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e182">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e192" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e184">Boetius, <title>de Consolatione</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e192">Tristes esse voluptatum exitus, quisquis
              reminisci libidinum suarum volet, intelliget: quae si beatos explicare possent, nihil
              causae est, quin pecudes quoque beatae esse dicantur, quarum omnis ad explendam
              corporalem lasciviam festinat intentio.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e197">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e204" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e199">Glossa interlinearis</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e204">Nihil voluptuosum, nihil suave placet Deo; sed
              quod habet aliquid mordacitatis et severitatis: unde pascha cum amaritudinibus
              manducatur.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e209">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e216" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e211">Glossa</ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e216">Voluptas insatiabilis est, et habita famem, non
              satietatem parit.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-d1e221">
          <ref corresp="#UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e231" xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Rd1e223">Seneca, in <title>Epistola</title>
          </ref>
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="UUyf3f-d1e31719-Qd1e231">Voluptates praecipue exturba, et invisissimas
              habe: latronum more in hoc nos amplectuntur, ut strangulent.</quote>
          </cit>
        </p>
      </div>
